diff_sketch_decider_critical_paths.after:
// Before re-declaring an existing critical of category in {phantom_integration, phantom_resolution, stale_citation}: 
// 1. Read the original review file path from issue.related_review or issue.source.
// 2. Re-extract the cited claim (e.g. "docs/index.html line 673 says 'annular solar eclipse'").
// 3. Re-test against current HEAD: git show origin/main:docs/index.html | sed -n '670,680p' | grep -q 'annular solar eclipse'.
// 4. If grep fails (cited problem GONE): write to daily-report internal_issues entry { issue_id, status:'stale_false_alarm', stale_at:<now>, stale_reason:'cited problem resolved between review write and decider read' } AND mark the original review file processed by appending its filename to monitor/decisions/processed-reviews.json. Do NOT re-declare critical.
// 5. If grep passes (cited problem persists): re-declare critical normally.
